Sentencas: A methane-fueled solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating at 500-650 degrees C was fabricated using a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-delta (BZCYYb) electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: Thin BZCYYb electrolyte films (thickness = 3 mu m) and NiO-BZCYYb anode supports were prepared by electron beam vapor deposition.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: A LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 catalyst layer was coated onto the anode support.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: The BZCYYb electrolyte film was characterized by X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: Current-voltage (I-V) curves and impedance spectra were measured to characterize the electrochemical performance of the cell.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: The NiO-BZCYYb anode exhibited a high coking resistance, and the cell was stable for 200 h when operated under methane at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: The presence of the LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 functional catalyst significantly enhanced the cell performance.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the prepared cells were 0.98, 0.65, 0.51 and 0.40 W cm(-2) at 650, 600, 550 and 500 degrees C, respectively, under methane fuel.
Titulo: A methane-fueled SOFC based on a thin BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ electrolyte film and a LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 anode functional layer
